From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 13:25:15 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/damon/core: trace esz at first setup

DAMON traces effective size quota starting from second update, only if a
change has made by the update.  In other words, the initial effective
size quota is not traced.  When there is no quota goals or 'temporal'
goal tuner is used, absence of initial quota makes it difficult to
understand under what effective quota DAMOS is running.  Trace the
initial value, too.

Signed-off-by: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
---
 mm/damon/core.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/damon/core.c b/mm/damon/core.c
index 1855e0c2a3031..f3129e1c2a3dc 100644
--- a/mm/damon/core.c
+++ b/mm/damon/core.c
@@ -2738,6 +2738,8 @@ static void damos_adjust_quota(struct damon_ctx *c, struct damos *s)
 	if (!quota->total_charged_sz && !quota->charged_from) {
 		quota->charged_from = jiffies;
 		damos_set_effective_quota(quota);
+		if (trace_damos_esz_enabled())
+			damos_trace_esz(c, s, quota);
 	}
 
 	/* New charge window starts */
-- 
2.47.3

